.TH XYOSC 1 "2026" "0.0.2" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
xyosc \- a simple XY-oscilloscope written in Go
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B xyosc
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B xyosc
is a real-time audio visualizer with multiple display modes. It captures audio
from a system device and renders it in an OpenGL window. The window is
undecorated and screen-transparent by default, making it suitable for use as
an overlay.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-beatdetect
Enable beat detection, overriding the value set in the configuration file.
.TP
.BI \-gain " float"
Override the gain multiplier. The value defined in the configuration file is
used by default. (default: \-1, meaning "use config")
.TP
.BI \-height " int"
Override the window height in pixels. (default: 1000)
.TP
.BI \-hi " float"
High frequency cutoff as a fraction of the sample rate. Activates the
frequency filter. Discernible details are around 0.001 increments for a 4096
buffer at 192\~kHz. (default: 1.0)
.TP
.BI \-lo " float"
Low frequency cutoff as a fraction of the sample rate. Activates the
frequency filter. Discernible details are around 0.001 increments for a 4096
buffer at 192\~kHz. (default: 0.0)
.TP
.B \-mix
Mix the left and right audio channels together, instead of using a single
channel for the single-axis oscilloscope mode.
.TP
.BI \-mode " int"
Override the default display mode on startup. See
.B MODES
below.
.TP
.B \-peakdetect
Enable peak detection, overriding the value set in the configuration file.
.TP
.B \-resizable
Toggle whether the window is resizable, inverting the value defined in the
configuration file.
.TP
.B \-right
Use the right audio channel instead of the left in single-axis oscilloscope
mode.
.TP
.BI \-width " int"
Override the window width in pixels. (default: 1000)
.TP
.BI \-x " int"
Override the starting X coordinate of the center of the window. A value of 0
corresponds to the center of the screen. (default: \-1, meaning centered)
.TP
.BI \-y " int"
Override the starting Y coordinate of the center of the window. A value of 0
corresponds to the center of the screen. (default: \-1, meaning centered)
.SH MODES
The display mode can be set at launch with
.B \-mode
or cycled at runtime with
.BR F .
The following integer values are accepted:
.TP
.B 0
XY oscilloscope (Lissajous). Left channel on the X axis, right on the Y axis.
.TP
.B 1
Single-channel oscilloscope. Displays a time-domain waveform for one channel.
.TP
.B 2
Frequency bars (FFT spectrum).
.TP
.B 3
VU meter. Displays per-channel loudness on a logarithmic or linear scale.
.TP
.B 4
Frequency bars with waterfall.
.TP
.B 5
Waterfall only.
.SH KEYBOARD SHORTCUTS
.TP
.B F
Cycle to the next display mode.
.TP
.B P
Cycle to the next shader preset for the current mode.
.SH CONFIGURATION
The configuration file is a YAML file created automatically on first launch at:
.PP
.RS
.I $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/ontake/xyosc/config.yml
.RE
.PP
On most systems this resolves to
.IR ~/.config/ontake/xyosc/config.yml .
If the file does not exist it is written with the compiled-in defaults.
Changes to the file are
.I not
hot-reloaded; restart xyosc to apply them.
.PP
The file is structured as a YAML document. The top-level keys and their
notable sub-keys are described below. Default values are shown in parentheses.
.SS App
.TP
.B App.TargetFPS
Target ticks per second. (240)
.TP
.B App.FPSCounter
Show a TPS counter in the corner. (false)
.TP
.B App.DefaultMode
Mode to start in. See
.B MODES
above. (0)
.TP
.B App.Splash.Enable
Show a splash screen on startup. (true)
.TP
.B App.Splash.StaticSecs
Seconds the splash is held fully visible. (1.0)
.TP
.B App.Splash.TransSecs
Seconds of fade transition. (1.0)
.SS Window
.TP
.B Window.Width / Window.Height
Initial window dimensions in pixels. (1000 × 1000)
.TP
.B Window.Resizable
Allow the window to be resized by the user. (false)
.SS Fonts
.TP
.B Fonts.UseSystemFont
Use a system-installed font instead of the built-in one. (true)
.TP
.B Fonts.SystemFont
Font family name to look up. ("Maple Mono NF")
.SS Audio
.TP
.B Audio.CaptureDeviceMatchIndex
Index of the capture device to prefer. (0)
.TP
.B Audio.CaptureDeviceMatchName
Substring to match against device names. ("" = any)
.TP
.B Audio.CaptureDeviceMatchSampleRate
Preferred sample rate for device selection. (0 = any)
.TP
.B Audio.SampleRate
Sample rate used for capture and all frequency calculations, in Hz. (192000)
.TP
.B Audio.Gain
Amplitude multiplier applied to all modes. (1.0)
.SS Buffers
Controls internal ring buffer and read buffer sizes. Increasing
.B Buffers.AudioCaptureBufferSize
reduces latency at the cost of CPU.
.SS Colors
.TP
.B Colors.UseConfigColorsInsteadOfPywal
When true, use the hex colors defined in
.B Colors.Palette
instead of reading from pywal's cache. (true)
.TP
.B Colors.Palette.Accent / .First / .Third / .Particle / .BG
Hex color strings used for the line, particle, and background colors.
.TP
.B Colors.BGOpacity
Background opacity, 0–255. (200)
.TP
.B Colors.DisableBGTransparency
Fill the background with a solid color instead of rendering transparent. (false)
.SS Line
Controls the rendered trace appearance.
.TP
.B Line.Opacity
Base opacity of the drawn line, 0–255. (200)
.TP
.B Line.Brightness
Multiplier applied to the line color. (1.0)
.TP
.B Line.ThicknessXY / .ThicknessSingleChannel
Stroke width in pixels for each mode. (3)
.TP
.B Line.OpacityAlsoAffectsThickness
Scale stroke width proportionally with computed opacity. (true)
.TP
.B Line.InvSqrtOpacityControl.Enable
Reduce opacity of fast-moving segments (dense regions appear dimmer). (true)
.TP
.B Line.TimeDependentOpacityControl.Enable
Fade older samples toward transparency. (true)
.SS ImageRetention
.TP
.B ImageRetention.Enable
Retain the previous frame with alpha decay (persistence / phosphor effect). (true)
.TP
.B ImageRetention.AlphaDecayBase / .AlphaDecaySpeed
Control the decay rate. Lower base = faster fade. (0.0000001, 2.0)
.SS Scale
Controls axis lines, tick marks, and labels shown in XY and single-channel modes.
.TP
.B Scale.Enable
Show the scale overlay. (true)
.TP
.B Scale.MainAxisEnable
Draw the central X and Y axis lines. (true)
.TP
.B Scale.Horz.Divs / Scale.Vert.Divs
Number of scale divisions on each axis. (20)
.TP
.B Scale.HorzDivDynamicPos
Rescale horizontal tick positions dynamically based on visible time span. (true)
.SS BeatDetection
.TP
.B BeatDetection.Enable
Run beat detection in a background thread. (true)
.TP
.B BeatDetection.ShowBPM
Render the detected BPM as text. (true)
.TP
.B BeatDetection.MaxBPM
Upper BPM limit used when searching for beat peaks. (500.0)
.TP
.B BeatDetection.HalfDisplayedBPM
Display half the detected BPM value (useful for half-time feels). (false)
.TP
.B BeatDetection.Metronome.Enable
Show a visual metronome indicator. (true)
.TP
.B BeatDetection.Metronome.ThinLineMode
Use a thin sweeping line instead of a filled bar. (true)
.TP
.B BeatDetection.Metronome.EdgeMode
Pulse the screen edges instead of drawing a bar. (false)
.SS Bars
Controls the FFT spectrum bar display (mode 2 and 4).
.TP
.B Bars.AutoGain.Enable
Automatically normalize bar heights to the loudest bin. (true)
.TP
.B Bars.PhaseColors.Enable
Color bars according to their FFT phase. (false)
.TP
.B Bars.PeakCursor.Enable
Show a floating cursor at the loudest frequency bin. (false)
.TP
.B Bars.PeakCursor.ShowNote
Display the musical note name next to the frequency. (true)
.TP
.B Bars.PeakCursor.RefNoteFreq
Reference frequency for A4 used in note calculation, in Hz. (440.0)
.SS VU
Controls the VU meter display (mode 3).
.TP
.B VU.LogScale
Use a dB (logarithmic) scale. (true)
.TP
.B VU.LogMaxDB / .LogMinDB
Top and bottom of the dB scale. (3, \-40)
.TP
.B VU.Peak.Enable
Show a peak-hold line. (true)
.TP
.B VU.Peak.HistorySeconds
How long the peak is held before decaying, in seconds. (5.0)
.SS Waterfall
Controls the waterfall display (modes 4 and 5).
.TP
.B Waterfall.Speed
Scroll speed in pixels per second. (165.0)
.SS Shaders
.TP
.B Shaders.Enable
Apply post-processing shader effects. (true)
.TP
.B Shaders.ModePresetsList
A list of shader preset index lists, one entry per mode, selecting which
presets from
.B Shaders.Presets
are active per mode.
.TP
.B Shaders.CustomShaderCode
A map of named Kage shader programs that can be referenced in presets.
.SS MPRIS
.TP
.B MPRIS.Enable
Show currently playing media information sourced from MPRIS. (false)
.SS FilterInfo
.TP
.B FilterInfo.Enable
Display active low/high cutoff frequencies in the corner when a filter is
applied. (true)
.SH COLORS AND THEMING
By default xyosc uses the hex color palette defined in the configuration file.
If
.B Colors.UseConfigColorsInsteadOfPywal
is set to false, xyosc reads colors from pywal's cache file at
.I $XDG_CACHE_HOME/wal/colors
and watches it for changes, updating the palette live whenever pywal rewrites
the file.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/ontake/xyosc/config.yml
Main configuration file (XDG_CONFIG_HOME).
.TP
.I ~/.cache/wal/colors
pywal color cache read when
.B Colors.UseConfigColorsInsteadOfPywal
is false.
